Observations on the data¶

  • The currency is Georgian Lari = 0.35 Euro (as some Georgian words have een spotted in the dataset ex: )
  • Creating the age column = 2020 - Year of production (Done below )
  • There is a word "" means "other"
    • The word will need to be replaced, (Done below )
  • Some of the used cars have 0 km Mileage.
    • The cars with 0 km Mileage with manuf year before 2018 will be removed as old cars can't have zero mileage. (Done below )
  • Some of the used cars have more than 70,000 km annual Mileage which doesn't make sense even for business cars. https://www.everlance.com/blog/10-highest-mileage-vehicles
    • The cars with more than 70,000 km annual Mileage will be removed. (Done below )
  • The ID column isn't needed The ID column to be removed. (Done below )
  • The dataset has duplicates The dublicates to be removed. (Already Done )
  • The levy is "-" for some of the cars and the type is String
    • It will need to be replaced with 0 (type Int) (Done below )
    • Will need to be scaled. (Done below )
  • Leather interior is Yes/No To be encoded to 0 and 1. (Done below )
  • Engine volume is String, it has zero value which irrational, has turbo ot not
    • To converted be float. (Done below )
    • Create another column (Turbo 1/0) (Done below )
    • Remove the records with 0 (Done below )
    • To be scaled (Done below )
  • Doors need correction
    • It is written as a date instead of ranges i.e 04May instead of 4 to 5 doors to be deleted. (Done below )
    • The doors column will be converted to minDoors (int). (Done below )
    • The values Will need to be scaled. (Done below )
  • The price is irrational max 26307500 and many cars under 4000 Georgian Lari wich non realistic after checking the average prices on the internet.

https://www.ap.ge/en

https://www.mankana.com/en

https://www.auto.ge/en/

- Remove the item with price above 200000 or below 4000 (Done below )
- Remove the outliers (Done below )
- The vlue will need to be scaled (Done below )
  • The millage of some of the cars is irrational = 999999999 km (which isn't possible)
    • Remove the items with price of 999999999 km (Done below )
    • Remove the outliers (Done below )
    • Millage to be converted from string to int (Done below )
    • The vlue will need to be scaled (Done below )
  • The wheels either Left wheel or Right-hand drive
    • Change Left/Yes to 1/0 (Done below )
  • The Cylinders will need to be scaled (Done below )
  • The Prod. year will need to be scaled (Done below )
  • The Fuel type , Model , Drive wheels , Color , Category , Gear box type and Manufacturer columns will need to be encoded.

Trials have been done to measue the effect of the following 31 varialbles to get the best accuracy:

Effect on test accuracy from -2 to +2

1   Mapping with values_count  -2

2   Mapping with mean price  +2

3   Mapping with sum price  -1

4   Mapping with median price  +1

5   Dropping the Price outliers  +2

6   Price outlers 10 to 90 % quantile  +2

7   Price outlers 25 to 75 % quantile  +1

8   Changing the bad data from 4000 to 2000 Georgian     -1

9   Dropping the outliers of Engine volume  +1

10  Dropping the outliers of Levy  +1

11  Dropping the outliers of Model  -1

12  Dropping the outliers of Airbags  -1

13  Dropping the outliers of Prod year  -1

14  Dropping the outliers of Turbo  -1

15  Dropping the outliers of Manufacturer  +1

16  Excluding "Levy"  -2

17  Excluding "Cylinders"  -1

18  Excluding "Drive wheels"  +1

19  Excluding "Manufacturer'"  -1

20  Excluding "Mileage"  -1

21  Excluding "minDoors"  0

22  Excluding "airbags"  -1

23  Excluding "Turbo"  -1

24  Excluding "Prod. Year"  -1

25  Excluding "Category"  +1

26  Standard scaler  -1

27  MinMax Scaler  0

28  RobustScaler  -1

29  PowerTransformer  -1

30  Trial to impute the wrong  milage bu KNN instead of dropping it  -1

31  Dropping the irrational Mileage  +2

# Engine volume from String to float and dropping the 0 Engine volume records

df_3.drop(df_3[df_3['Engine volume']=='0'].index,inplace = True)

def turboCheck(x):
    if ' Turbo' in x:
        x.replace(' Turbo','')
        return 1
    else:
        return 0

def cleanEngineVol(y):
    if ' ' in y:
        return float(y.partition(" ")[0])
    else:
        return float(y)

# Creating the Turbo column from Engine volume

df_3['Turbo'] = df_3['Engine volume'].apply(turboCheck)

df_3['Engine volume'] = df_3['Engine volume'].apply(cleanEngineVol)

def doorsCorrection(x):
    if 'May' in x:
        return 3
    elif 'Mar' in x:
        return 2
    elif '>' in x:
        return 1

def wheelsCorrection(x):
    if 'Left' in x:
        return 1
    elif 'Right' in x:
        return 0

#Generating the minDoor column

df_3['minDoors'] = df_3['Doors'].apply(doorsCorrection)

# Converting the wheels from Left and Right to 1 and 0

df_3['Wheel'] = df_3['Wheel'].apply(wheelsCorrection)

#Cleaning the mileage column

def mileageCorrection(x):
    if ' km' in x:
        x_2 = int(x.partition(" ")[0])
        if x_2 == 0 or x_2 > 4828032:
            return None
        else:
            return x_2



df_3['Mileage'] = df_3['Mileage'].apply(mileageCorrection)

# Dropping the null records

df_3 = df_3.dropna() 

# Removing the wrong mileage (old cars with 0 mileage)

wrong_mileeage = df_3[(df_3['Mileage']==0) & (df_3['Prod. year']<2018)]

df_3.drop(wrong_mileeage.index,inplace=True)

#The max car annual mileage

wrong_mileeage_2 = df_3[ ((df_3['Mileage'] / (2021 - df_3['Prod. year'])) > 70000)]

df_3.drop(wrong_mileeage_2.index,inplace=True)

# Removing Manufacturer outliers

Q1 = df_3_s['Manufacturer'].quantile(0.25) # 0.25 can be changed
Q3 = df_3_s['Manufacturer'].quantile(0.75) # 0.75 can be changed

IQR = Q3 - Q1

lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
outliers = df_3_s[(df_3_s['Manufacturer'] > upper) | (df_3_s['Manufacturer'] < lower)].index 


df_3_s.drop(outliers,inplace=True)
